‚ñ∫ Common Candlestick Patterns: https://www.ig.com/en/trading-strategies/16-candlestick-patterns-every-trader-should-know-180615
‚ñ∫ Top 10 Technical Indicators: https://www.ig.com/en/trading-strategies/10-trading-indicators-every-trader-should-know-190604
‚ñ∫ Technical Analysis for Cryptocurrency: https://www.coinbureau.com/education/crypto-technical-analysis/

~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

‚ùìWhat is Technical Analysis‚ùì

Technical Analysis is based on human psychology, namely emotions like fear and greed. It posits that these emotions are ultimately what drive prices up or down, and that these emotions create visible patterns which repeat themselves. This means that with the right methodology, the future price action of an asset can be predicted using technical analysis. 

Technical analysis was invented almost 300 years ago by a Japanese rice merchant name Hunma Munehisa, who is believed to be the most successful trader of all time. He wrote the first book on market psychology, and the principles he defined continue to be used in technical trading today. 

üìàTechnical vs. Fundamental Analysisüìâ

Technical Analysis focuses exclusively on price and does not pay much attention to fundamentals. For cryptocurrencies, fundamental factors include things like tokenomics, network activity, the strength of the project‚Äôs development team, and any notable partnerships the project has. These fundamentals are often used by HODLers and more experienced traders to gauge the long-term price potential of an asset. 

Given that the average cryptocurrency trader is irrational, many believe that technical analysis is more effective than fundamental analysis for this reason. As a rule of thumb, technical analysis should be used for shorter term trading whereas fundamental analysis should be used for long term trading. A combination of both is necessary to ensure a clear picture of the cryptocurrency you are trading. 

ü§∑‚Äç‚ôÇ‚ÄçHow To Use Candlestick Chartsü§∑‚Äç‚ôÇ‚Äç

Technical trading centers around candlestick charts. Each candlestick consists of a body and a wick, and each candlestick marks a single unit of the period you have set the chart to (e.g. 1 hour, 1 day). When you see a candle with a long wick at the top, it suggests that traders are taking profits and price could drop. When you see a candle with a long wick at the bottom, this suggests that traders are buying the dip and price could pump.
 
Support and resistance lines can be drawn using the tops and bottoms of candles within a given timeframe. These reveal various shapes, most notably triangles, that have been used for hundreds of years to predict future price action. 

üìäTrading Volumeüìä 

Trading volume is used to confirm the strength of a price trend. If price is quickly moving up or down but the volume is dropping, the trend is not very strong. A high amount of volume as price changes confirms that a breakout to the upside or downside.  

üìçThe Best Technical Indicatorsüìç

The MACD, the RSI, and Bollinger Bands are some of the most popular indicators in cryptocurrency trading. Moving averages allow you to spot possible support and resistance points as well as forecast future price activity. 

The RSI helps you determine whether an asset is overpriced or undervalued. The Bollinger Band indicator tracks the price volatility of an asset, occasionally revealing when you should buy or sell depending on whether the price has gone outside/below or outside/above of the Bollinger Band range, respectively.

description:

The XRP price has maintained a steep ascending trend ever since the token rebounded from the March 2020 lows. The price further went up by more than 1000% and also encountered a drastic bear market, losing over 80% of its gains. Regardless of the bullish or bearish trend prevailing within the market, the XRP price held the lower ascending trend line, which has been acting as a strong support since then. Now that the price has soared beyond its bearish reach, the token is believed to mark a dollar milestone anytime from now. 
The XRP price jumps by over 20% in just a few hours, aiming to reach levels above $0.8, which may occur anytime from now. With this, the optimism around XRP has surged as the token lands up as one of the top performers compared to the last several days, largely driven by memecoins. After remaining behind the crypto market trends for a long time, the XRP price has finally triggered a bullish trend. 
#ripple #xrp #sec

title: How to identify Crypto Trends like a Pro? Uptrend, Downtrend, Sideways Trends explained
description:
Support & resistance levels can be identified easily with trend lines, which help crypto traders find the right buy, sell & trade opportunities in the market. This makes understanding trend lines study a very important aspect of technical analysis.
Uptrends are an indication of prices reaching higher highs & lower lows, while Downtrend showcases the opposite. Trends study can truly be a crypto traders friend and help them time the market well.
For more on the different types of trends and how to identify them, watch this video till the end.

title: Crypto Market Gets Trumped
description: In this episode of the Crypto Trends Podcast, hosted by Robert Croak and Armando Pantoja, the discussion focuses on the effects of Donald Trump's election victory on the cryptocurrency and blockchain markets. They analyze Bitcoin's recent all-time high amidst Trump's win, the role of prediction markets, and the impact of $541 million outflows just before the election. Predictions about Bitcoin's future, the influence of institutional investors, and the potential removal of SEC's Gary Gensler are also covered. The hosts discuss the launch of XRP's Price Oracle amendment and its implications. They then explore Nvidia's potential investment in Elon Musk's AI startup, XAI, and the synergy across Musk's ventures. Finally, they emphasize the bullish outlook for crypto and AI due to the Trump presidency, highlighting several promising cryptocurrencies and stocks like Near Protocol and MicroStrategy.

In the world of technical analysis, there are 2 types of market that exists, trending markets, and ranging markets.

Trending market, is when the price is clearly moving in a definitive direction. Ranging markets on the other hand, is a type of market where the price moves erratically without having a definitive direction

Usually traders tend to avoid ranging markets, because it‚Äôs a lot harder to predict where the price will go next. Unfortunately, ranging markets are unavoidable, in fact study shows that most of the time, markets are actually ranging

"Bitcoin, the largest cryptocurrency, dropped 6% to $92,446, retreating further from the $100,000 milestone. The entire crypto market cap fell to $3.35 trillion, with other tokens like Ether and Solana also in the red."

description:

~~~~~

- TIMESTAMPS -
0:00 Intro
2:12 History of Sentiment Analysis 
5:10 How Does Sentiment Analysis Work 
8:16 Sentiment Analysis In Cryptocurrency 
9:26 Cryptocurrency Fear And Greed Index  
11:44 Bitcoin Bull & Bear Index  
14:07 Cryptoradar 
15:32 Santiment & LunarCrush  
17:94 Altcoin Sentiment Analysis Trading   
18:43 Conclusion

~~~~~

‚õìÔ∏è üîó Useful Links üîó ‚õìÔ∏è

‚ñ∫ History Of Sentiment Analysis: https://arxiv.org/ftp/arxiv/papers/1612/1612.01556.pdf
‚ñ∫ How Sentiment Analysis Works (In Detail): https://monkeylearn.com/sentiment-analysis/
‚ñ∫ Cryptocurrency Fear And Greed Index: https://alternative.me/crypto/fear-and-greed-index/
‚ñ∫ Stock Market Fear And Greed Index: https://money.cnn.com/data/fear-and-greed/?iid=EL
‚ñ∫ Bitcoin Bull And Bear Index: https://www.augmento.ai/bitcoin-sentiment/
‚ñ∫ Bison Cryptoradar: https://bisonapp.com/en/cryptoradar/
‚ñ∫ Santiment: https://santiment.net/
‚ñ∫ LunarCrush: https://lunarcrush.com/markets?rpp=50
‚ñ∫ Sentiment Analysis ‚ÄúPredicts‚Äù Altcoin Prices: https://www.frontiersin.org/articles/10.3389/fphy.2019.00098/full

~~~~~

üìöHistory Of Sentiment Analysisüìö

Sentiment analysis has been around for a long time but it took off in the early 2000s as social media platforms started to emerge

It was first used by online shopping giants like Amazon and politicians like Barack Obama to gauge public opinion without having to read every single comment. As of about 2010, sentiment is used for trading

üë®‚Äçüè´How Does Sentiment Analysis Work?üë®‚Äçüè´

In a sentence, sentiment analysis involves analyzing a text to determine whether it is positive, negative, or neutral

This is done by assigning a score to each word depending on how negative or positive it is, and then adding all those scores together to see what the overall sentiment of the text is

üìäSentiment Analysis In Cryptocurrency Tradingüìä

If you can detect the emotions of investors in advance with sentiment analysis on say, social media platforms like Twitter and Reddit, you could theoretically predict the price action of any cryptocurrency

üò±Bitcoin Fear And Greed Index ü§ë 

The fear and greed index for cryptocurrency is modeled after the fear and greed index for the stock market which was created by CNN‚Äôs financial division. Both are updated on a daily basis

Like the fear and greed index for the stock market, the fear and greed index for cryptocurrency is created using an aggregate of metrics that are also worth looking at separately

üêÇBitcoin Bull And Bear Indexüêª

In contrast to the fear and greed index, the bull and bear index focuses exclusively on bitcoin sentiment on social media platforms, specifically Bitcointalk, Reddit, and Twitter

More importantly, the bull and bear index is updated every hour which makes it more suitable for active day trading.
üîéCryptoradarüîé

The cryptoradar tracks social media sentiment for Bitcoin, Bitcoin Cash, Ethereum, Litecoin, and XRP in real time

üë®‚ÄçüíªSantiment And LunarCrushüë®‚Äçüíª 

LunarCrush tracks over 2 thousand cryptocurrencies, and you can rank them using any of the 27 sentiment and price-based indicators LunarCrush offers

Like LunarCrush, Santiment tracks a series of social sentiment metrics using data from Twitter, Reddit, and even Telegram for nearly 2000 coins and tokens

üí∏Altcoin Sentiment Analysis Tradingüí∏

Sentiment analysis‚Äô forecasting features are more powerful for mid and small cap altcoins. This is because their price discovery is more organic as they are not the focus of market manipulation

Even though many mid and small cap altcoins are also manipulated from time to time, usually that manipulation is coordinated through social media

Because most if not all this information is out in the open, sentiment analysis indicators can often let you get in early and sell right as that pump is peaking

Even so, be weary of how that sentiment data is being collected

~~~~~

üë®‚Äçüè´Cryptocurrency 101üë®‚Äçüè´ 

Put simply, cryptocurrencies are like regular currencies except they‚Äôre entirely digital. Each individual cryptocurrency coin is fundamentally just a collection of numbers and letters

This sounds complicated, but it‚Äôs actually not far off from what we see with currencies today. Bills have serial numbers, and bank accounts have account numbers

Cryptocurrencies are basically like serial numbers without the physical bill, and cryptocurrency wallets are like bank account numbers without your name attached to them

Instead of the bank or government keeping track of your wallet balance, this is done by computers that connect to a cryptocurrency network to process transactions and earn cryptocurrency for doing so

üôã‚Äç‚ôÇ‚ÄçQuestions About Bitcoin, Dogecoin, Ethereum etc.üôã‚Äç‚ôÇ‚Äç
  
Broadly speaking there are two types of cryptocurrencies: coins and tokens. Cryptocurrency coins belong to cryptocurrency networks that were built from the ground up

Because cryptocurrency networks are so hard to make from scratch, only a few dozen cryptocurrencies are actually coins. The rest are cryptocurrency tokens

The most important thing to remember about cryptocurrency tokens is that a lot of them are nothing more than scams. This is primarily because cryptocurrency tokens are so easy to create

‚öñCryptocurrency Safety And Criminal Use Concerns‚öñ 
   
For starters, not all cryptocurrencies are created equal. Some cryptocurrencies are built to prioritize speed over security, and usually the consequences of that play out quite quickly

When it comes to the criminal activities, it is true that ransom demands made by hackers often involve some kind of cryptocurrency. However, these cryptocurrencies always get swapped to privacy coins

üí∞Explaining Cryptocurrency Price And Valueüí∞ 

Bitcoin has value because its BTC coin has an economic profile to gold. It has a maximum supply and only a small amount of BTC is created each day, and that amount is cut in half every 4 years

Cryptocurrencies like Ethereum‚Äôs ETH have value because they are required to pay for the transaction fees associated with minting and moving tokens as well as using decentralized applications

ü§ë‚ÄúOkay, Which Cryptocurrencies Should I Buy?‚Äùü§ë

Before you answer that question, you must remember to emphasize that nothing you tell them is financial or investment advice

Which cryptocurrencies you decide to invest in boils down to your timeline and risk tolerance. Make sure not to mix up market cap with price potential, and always do your own research.

‚ñ∫ How Sentiment Analysis Works (In Detail): https://monkeylearn.com/sentiment-analysis/
‚ñ∫ Cryptocurrency Fear And Greed Index: https://alternative.me/crypto/fear-and-greed-index/
‚ñ∫ Stock Market Fear And Greed Index: https://money.cnn.com/data/fear-and-greed/?iid=EL
‚ñ∫ Bitcoin Bull And Bear Index: https://www.augmento.ai/bitcoin-sentiment/
‚ñ∫ Bison Cryptoradar: https://bisonapp.com/en/cryptoradar/
‚ñ∫ Santiment: https://santiment.net/
‚ñ∫ LunarCrush: https://lunarcrush.com/markets?rpp=50
‚ñ∫ Sentiment Analysis ‚ÄúPredicts‚Äù Altcoin Prices: https://www.frontiersin.org/articles/10.3389/fphy.2019.00098/full

~~~~~

üìöHistory Of Sentiment Analysisüìö

Sentiment analysis has been around for a long time but it took off in the early 2000s as social media platforms started to emerge

It was first used by online shopping giants like Amazon and politicians like Barack Obama to gauge public opinion without having to read every single comment. As of about 2010, sentiment is used for trading

üë®‚Äçüè´How Does Sentiment Analysis Work?üë®‚Äçüè´

In a sentence, sentiment analysis involves analyzing a text to determine whether it is positive, negative, or neutral

This is done by assigning a score to each word depending on how negative or positive it is, and then adding all those scores together to see what the overall sentiment of the text is

üìäSentiment Analysis In Cryptocurrency Tradingüìä

If you can detect the emotions of investors in advance with sentiment analysis on say, social media platforms like Twitter and Reddit, you could theoretically predict the price action of any cryptocurrency

üò±Bitcoin Fear And Greed Index ü§ë 

The fear and greed index for cryptocurrency is modeled after the fear and greed index for the stock market which was created by CNN‚Äôs financial division. Both are updated on a daily basis

Like the fear and greed index for the stock market, the fear and greed index for cryptocurrency is created using an aggregate of metrics that are also worth looking at separately

üêÇBitcoin Bull And Bear Indexüêª

In contrast to the fear and greed index, the bull and bear index focuses exclusively on bitcoin sentiment on social media platforms, specifically Bitcointalk, Reddit, and Twitter

More importantly, the bull and bear index is updated every hour which makes it more suitable for active day trading.
üîéCryptoradarüîé

The cryptoradar tracks social media sentiment for Bitcoin, Bitcoin Cash, Ethereum, Litecoin, and XRP in real time

üë®‚ÄçüíªSantiment And LunarCrushüë®‚Äçüíª 

LunarCrush tracks over 2 thousand cryptocurrencies, and you can rank them using any of the 27 sentiment and price-based indicators LunarCrush offers

Like LunarCrush, Santiment tracks a series of social sentiment metrics using data from Twitter, Reddit, and even Telegram for nearly 2000 coins and tokens

üí∏Altcoin Sentiment Analysis Tradingüí∏

Sentiment analysis‚Äô forecasting features are more powerful for mid and small cap altcoins. This is because their price discovery is more organic as they are not the focus of market manipulation

Even though many mid and small cap altcoins are also manipulated from time to time, usually that manipulation is coordinated through social media

Because most if not all this information is out in the open, sentiment analysis indicators can often let you get in early and sell right as that pump is peaking

Even so, be weary of how that sentiment data is being collected

~~~~~

title: Crypto Market Highlights: Key Developments and Trends Shaping the Digital Asset Landscape
description:
- Bitcoin reaches $35,000 as investor interest grows
- Ethereum developer activity hits all-time high, driving major dApp scaling
- Ripple wins partial SEC case victory, XRP rises 10%
- Binance expands into NFTs, drawing millions to new marketplace
- Cardano launches smart contracts, ADA rises 5%
- Dogecoin up 15% following Elon Musk‚Äôs tweet
- DeFi attracts billions, benefiting Ethereum and Solana
- Solana experiences temporary network outage, quickly resolved
- Polkadot launching parachains, enhancing interoperability
- Governments consider stablecoin regulations amid popularity rise
- Shiba Inu prices spike 20%, meme coin interest remains high
- Chainlink secures key finance partnerships, boosting adoption
- El Salvador plans Bitcoin City expansion, aiming for crypto hub status
- NFTs revolutionizing art market, Ethereum holds 90% market share
- Litecoin‚Äôs next halving in mid-2025, expected price impact
- Ethereum nears Proof of Stake transition, promising lower fees
- Privacy coins face regulatory scrutiny, some exchanges delisting
- Bitcoin mining shifts offshore, driven by energy-friendly regions
- Blockchain-based games gain popularity with play-to-earn incentives
- Crypto airdrops as a popular marketing tool, attracting users
- Stellar Lumens secures financial institution partnerships
- DeFi hacks increase, highlighting security risks
- Bitcoin‚Äôs first ETF launches, attracting institutional interest
- Crypto credit cards emerge, blending finance and crypto
- South Korea imposes 20% crypto gains tax, affecting investors
- Avalanche‚Äôs AVAX enters top 10 by market cap, reflecting demand
- Central banks explore CBDCs, led by China, Europe, and the US
- Billionaire invests in Polygon‚Äôs MATIC, boosting Layer 2 interest
- Ethereum‚Äôs Shanghai upgrade on track to improve speed and fees
- China‚Äôs mining ban leads firms to relocate, diversifying Bitcoin‚Äôs network
- Japan mandates stablecoin transfer registrations, enhancing oversight
- Germany publishes crypto tax guidelines, setting a standard
- Shiba Inu developers plan DEX and staking, aiming for utility
- India expands digital rupee pilot across regions
- MicroStrategy buys $100 million in Bitcoin, strengthening holdings
- Ripple partners with major bank for international remittance

title: Does Technical Analysis Work In Crypto Market?
description:
Does technical analysis work in crypto market? This is a question that many people ask and they want to know if technical analysis really works in cryptocurrency market. To answer this question, in this video first it's explained what technical analysis is and what are the basics of technical analysis, and finally based on these facts about technical analysis, it's discussed if technical analysis work in crypto market or not.  
Technical analysis is a trading method that focuses on the price and movements of the prices over time, and technical analysis can be used for intraday trading, swing trading, mid-term trading and even long-term trading. Using technical analysis trading strategies in crypto market is widely used among traders, and many traders in cryptocurrency market use technical analysis chart patterns, indicators, and other concepts of technical analysis for taking trading decisions.

title: Buy or Sell? Master the Ascending Triangle Price Action Strategy
description:
Master the Ascending Triangle: A Powerful Price Action Trading Pattern!

Welcome to Rocket Stock Picks, where trading strategies meet simplicity. In this video, we unlock the secrets of the Ascending Triangle, a versatile pattern that signals both trend continuation and reversal, leading to strong upward movements.

üìà What is the Ascending Triangle?
The Ascending Triangle is a price action pattern where a horizontal resistance line meets an ascending trendline, showing a battle between buyers and sellers. This pattern often precedes a bullish breakout.

üìä Why the Ascending Triangle is Effective

Dual Potential: It signals both continuation and reversal of trends.
Breakout Power: A breakout above resistance often leads to significant price movement.
Volume Confirmation: Watch for increasing volume at the breakout point for added confidence.
üåê How to Trade the Ascending Triangle

Identify the horizontal resistance and ascending support lines.
Enter trades on the breakout above resistance.
Set a target equal to the height of the triangle for calculated profits.
Use volume spikes to confirm the pattern‚Äôs reliability.
üíπ Perfect for All Markets
Whether you‚Äôre trading Forex, stocks, or crypto, the Ascending Triangle offers high-probability setups across multiple timeframes and assets.

üéØ Why Rocket Stock Picks?
At Rocket Stock Picks, we simplify complex strategies, empowering you with actionable insights to excel in any market condition.

Hey this is Becker. I appreciate you reading this. It's important.

I love talking crypto, sharing what I am looking and making you laugh. That said I CANNOT STRESS how dangerous crypto is and how likely you are to lose money.

I have done dozens of polls over the years. USUALLY 85-95%+ of people that try crypto LEAVE IN LOSS. If you are new to this your chances of leaving in profit are EXTREMELY low.

Because of this my #1 suggestion is DO NOT TRADE CRYPTO. If you do make sure its with low amounts of money because the odds are you will lose it.

Please ALSO know
A) The coins I mentioned have NO GUARANTEE of working out. I do EXTREMELY high risk trading on my channel. These coins WILL crash hard at the end of the run. Many will even crash due to various things like hacks, bad PR or even being straight rugs. I do my best to avoid these but it happens in low caps.

THUS I SUGGEST A) DO NOT TRADE CRYPTO B) If you are new/can't afford to lose big stick to the top high market cap reputable coins.

B) I PLAN TO SELL ALL MY COINS AT SOME POINT. I WILL NOT ANNOUNCE IT. While I do my absolute best to not sell coins that I have recently mentioned (I have sold 2 out of 50+ coins I hold in the last year for example)...I will 100% sell my coins when I think the market is getting to a good sell point, overheated OR if I see an imminent crash coming.

These coins are NOT SAFE investments. Most of them do nothing. These are high risk bets on crypto narratives for fast short term profits. The goal is trade in and sell before a market crash and run for the hills. I am NEVER implying you should hold or treat these coins as serious investments.

This can happen fast. I like you want to leave in profit and if you are in these coins I will be selling at your expense JUST like you would do to me if you saw a good chance to sell.

This is dark. I get that. But this is crypto. I want to exit in profit and I want you to too. However that is not always the case and I want to be COMPLETELY transparent with you about my intent, what I hold and my sell strategies (which are all over this channel)

This is why I STRESS DO NOT BUY COINS I SUGGEST IF YOU ARE NOT WILLING TO TAKE THE RISK OF BEING OPPOSITE TO ME IN A TRADE. I provide tons of strategies to find your own coins.

C) I kind of suck at this. I've made a lot of money, but Ive lost a bunch of money too in bad coins. If you copy trade me I do not imply or suggest you will get good results. I am GAMBLING on this market and hoping it works out. I am not a trading expert or financial advisor. Even if my trades do win you should EXPECT to lose big on a few of them, as is the nature of crypto.

In conclusion :
I want you to win. This in mind CRYPTO is a financial gamble and almost guaranteed to lose you money your first few years in it. Even experienced traders/investors get wiped out here. I also plan to sell coins that I mentioned on this channel so if you are in coins I am in I could MAKE money at your expense.

If any of this sits badly with you PLEASE do not trade crypto, buy coins I mention. I am not even that good at trading.

Hugs n kisses.

title: Buy or Sell? Master the Ascending Triangle Price Action Strategy
description:
Master the Ascending Triangle: A Powerful Price Action Trading Pattern!

Welcome to Rocket Stock Picks, where trading strategies meet simplicity. In this video, we unlock the secrets of the Ascending Triangle, a versatile pattern that signals both trend continuation and reversal, leading to strong upward movements.

üìà What is the Ascending Triangle?
The Ascending Triangle is a price action pattern where a horizontal resistance line meets an ascending trendline, showing a battle between buyers and sellers. This pattern often precedes a bullish breakout.

üìä Why the Ascending Triangle is Effective

Dual Potential: It signals both continuation and reversal of trends.
Breakout Power: A breakout above resistance often leads to significant price movement.
Volume Confirmation: Watch for increasing volume at the breakout point for added confidence.
üåê How to Trade the Ascending Triangle

Identify the horizontal resistance and ascending support lines.
Enter trades on the breakout above resistance.
Set a target equal to the height of the triangle for calculated profits.
Use volume spikes to confirm the pattern‚Äôs reliability.
üíπ Perfect for All Markets
Whether you‚Äôre trading Forex, stocks, or crypto, the Ascending Triangle offers high-probability setups across multiple timeframes and assets.

title: Buy or Sell? Master the Bullish Flag Price Action Strategy
description:
Master the Bullish Flag Pattern: A Powerful Price Action Trading Strategy!

Welcome to Rocket Stock Picks! In this video, we dive into the dynamics of the Bullish Flag pattern‚Äîone of the most reliable and widely used price action trading strategies. Whether you‚Äôre into Forex, stocks, or cryptocurrencies, the Bullish Flag can guide you to profitable opportunities by signaling a continuation of the uptrend.

üìà What is a Bullish Flag?
The Bullish Flag is a continuation pattern characterized by a strong initial upward move (the pole) followed by a consolidation phase (the flag). This setup often leads to another breakout, presenting a high-probability trading opportunity.

üìä Step-by-Step Analysis

Identify the pole‚Äîa sharp upward move.
Recognize the flag, a tight consolidation channel.
Time your entry on the breakout above the flag‚Äôs resistance.
Use the pole‚Äôs length to set realistic profit targets.
üåê Universal Trading Application
The Bullish Flag works seamlessly across markets, whether you're trading Forex, stocks, or crypto. We'll demonstrate how to identify and trade this pattern for maximum returns.

üíπ Key Features for Success

Understand how volume confirms the breakout.
Learn to manage risk by placing stop-loss orders effectively.
Discover how to maximize gains by setting proper profit targets.
üéØ Why Rocket Stock Picks?
At Rocket Stock Picks, we simplify complex strategies and bring you actionable insights to navigate the markets with confidence. Whether you‚Äôre a beginner or an experienced trader, this video will elevate your skills.

title: A Beginner's Guide to Crypto Trading  #crypto #cryptotrading #shorts #cryptoforbeginners
description:
A Beginner's Guide to Crypto Trading

Are you curious about cryptocurrency trading but don‚Äôt know where to begin? You‚Äôre not alone! Many people are eager to jump into this exciting world. Here‚Äôs a simple guide to help you get started.

Step 1: Learn the Basics

Before you start trading, it‚Äôs important to understand some key concepts. Think of cryptocurrency like a new type of money, but instead of coins or bills, it lives online. Here are some basics to explore:

Blockchain: This is the technology that powers cryptocurrencies. Imagine it as a digital notebook that keeps track of all transactions in a secure way.

Bitcoin: Often called the first cryptocurrency, it's a good starting point to understand how digital currencies work.

Exchanges: These are platforms where you buy and sell cryptocurrencies, similar to how stock exchanges work for regular stocks.

You can find valuable resources on platforms like YouTube, online courses, or blogs. Just remember to take your time to really grasp these concepts.

Step 2: Practice on Demo Accounts

Once you have a grasp on the basics, it‚Äôs time to practice. Many exchanges offer demo accounts. These accounts let you trade with virtual money, so you can learn how to buy and sell without any risk.

Think of it as a driving simulator‚Äîyou can get plenty of practice without the fear of crashing! This step will help you build confidence before you start trading with real money.

Step 3: Stay Updated on Crypto News and Trends

The world of cryptocurrency is always changing. Market movements and news can greatly influence prices. To be a successful trader, you need to stay informed.

Follow trusted crypto news sources and keep an eye on market trends. Knowing what‚Äôs happening can help you make better trading decisions. It‚Äôs like following the weather before planning a picnic‚Äîbeing aware can save you from surprises!

Conclusion

Starting your journey in crypto trading can be thrilling if you follow the right steps. Remember to learn the basics, practice in a safe environment, and stay updated with the latest news. If you're ready to begin, check out https://becoin.net/ for more tips and resources. Your crypto adventure awaits!

Ready to trade? Follow us for daily tips and check out https://becoin.net/ to begin your crypto adventure today!

title: Is Bitcoin's Bottom Near? | Crypto Market Analysis
description:
This is the Altcoin with the strongest price increase in the first week of September 2024, let's update with the crypto market news channel.
Helium (HNT) skyrocketed 19% with strong buying pressure even though there were no major developments driving the price up.
The first week of September 2024 saw altcoins struggle to achieve significant growth as the overall market remained relatively quiet.
However, several coins in the top 100 by market capitalization bucked the overall trend, posting gains thanks to market interest and notable developments.
Among them are Helium (HNT), Starknet (STRK), and Uniswap (UNI), all of which have seen notable growth.
Helium (HNT)
HNT, the native token of Helium ‚Äì a decentralized blockchain platform for the Internet of Things, has increased by 19%. Analysis shows that there is no major event behind this increase.
From a technical perspective, the On Balance Volume (OBV) index has increased since late August. OBV measures trading volume to gauge buying and selling pressure; when OBV falls, this indicates more selling volume.
The increase in OBV on the daily chart shows increased accumulation, which contributed to pushing HNT price above $8. If the buying pressure continues, HNT could reach $8.51. However, if interest in the token declines, the price could drop to $6.88.
Starknet (STRK)
STRK, the native cryptocurrency of the Layer-2 Ethereum blockchain, suddenly appeared on the list of top altcoin price gainers this week. Since its launch, STRK has struggled to register significant price increases.
However, the token increased to $0.40 shortly after Vitalik Buterin, co-founder of Ethereum, transferred more than 2 million STRK tokens to a new wallet. Currently, STRK is trading at $0.43, after falling slightly to $0.39.
The Bull Bear Power Index (BBP) shows that bullish momentum has overcome bearish pressure, suggesting further growth is possible.
Additionally, STRK broke above the downtrend line, reinforcing the bullish outlook. If this trend continues, STRK price could rise to $0.48. Conversely, if the token breaks support at $0.35, it could drop to an all-time low.
Uniswap (UNI)
UNI is on the list of altcoins gaining in value thanks to the settlement of a dispute with the Commodity Futures Trading Commission (CTFC). Immediately after this information, UNI price increased to $6.40, bringing the total increase for the week to 8%.
Currently, UNI is trading at $6.22, down from its peak this week. On the daily chart, UNI is close to falling below its 20-day Moving Average (EMA).
Normally, a break above the EMA indicates a bullish trend, but if UNI drops below this level, the price could drop below $6 and reach $5.60.
The Relative Strength Index (RSI) also shows bearish momentum, reinforcing the bearish outlook. However, if there are positive developments for UNI, the price could rise to $6.91.
News from crypto market channels can provide valuable information and insight into cryptocurrency market trends and developments. If you have any questions or need more information about a specific topic in the crypto market, don't hesitate to leave a comment or question below the video.

title: This Is Not Financial Advice
description: Glauber "Pro" Contessoto-an immigrant working multiple jobs and living in a 220-square-foot apartment-gambles his life savings on a joke cryptocurrency.
